race.comment: THE LOUVRE (6) improved again winning this grade and track/trip, three weeks ago. Came from the back and will have to do the same here. Has a handy 3kg claim and with average luck, he can keep the ball rolling. AFFINITY FLYER (7) settled well back and didn't threatened over 1200m at Doomben last time out. Went well here prior to improve again. Will enjoy a drop in class and is a main contender. SUPER QUICK (10) continues to race well. Will race forward from an inside barrier and get every chance.  ENTERPRISE ATTACK (1) resumed over 1200m at Gold Coast, beaten 2.5 lengths. Proven second-up and will have trimmed down. Has a wide gate but is in the right race and is one of the better hopes. GALWAY HUSSLER (9) peaks in easier and went well enough at Kilcoy two back to suggest he can get into the frame. Has a 2kg claim and a handy draw.
